	dprr:hasNoteText "He interposed his veto of the Gabinian law (see above), amid scenes of great disorder, until the eighteenth tribe was summoned to vote on a motion for his recall from office (Cic. Corn. 1, fr. 30, and Ascon. 72 C; Dio 36.24.4, and 30.1-2)." .
